  "description": "Fired when a block is right-clicked by a tool to change its state. For example: Used to determine if an axe can strip , a shovel can path , or a hoe can till . This deprecated subclass event is only fired when BlockEvent.BlockToolModificationEvent.isSimulated() is false. To receive simulated events, use BlockEvent.BlockToolModificationEvent . This event is Cancelable . If canceled, this will prevent the tool from changing the block's state.",
